document_data.Usages:
* Beeswax was commonly used to make candles, which were often used in the practice of [[divine magic|clerical]] [[candle magic]].
* Beeswax was occasionally used by craftsmen in the [[Sword Coast]] for a variety of leatherwork and woodwork.
* An ointment for reducing tumors could be made by mixing beeswax with powdered [[jet]].<ref>{{Cite dragon/83/The many facets of gems|15}}
* Beeswax  could double as [[sealing wax]].<ref>
* Some sets of [[thieves' tools]] included a lump of beeswax in order to make impressions of keys.<ref>{{Cite dragon/115/Tools of the (Thieving) Trade|36}}
* Beeswax acted as a [[material component]] for a variety of [[spell]]s, including ''[[deafness]]'',<ref> [[inferno (spell)|''inferno'']], and ''[[tears of fire]]''.{{Cite dragon/268/Secrets of the Brotherhood of the True Flame|53}}
* The [[Zakhara]]n spell ''[[fire truth]]'', required a candle made from the beeswax of a rare species of desert bee as a material component.
